    <p style="text-align:center ;">
    <h1 class="w3-jumbo"><span class="w3-hide-small"></span> American Music Icons</h1>
    <h1 style="font-size: 25px;" >Welcome to our American Music Icons website. We are Alessia, Benedetta, Elisa and Riccardo, first year students of the second cycle degree in Language, Society and Communication at the University of Bologna.
      </style>
    <br>
    <br>When talking about music, many were the topics that came to our minds. Also, the website title “American Music Icons” is very wide and potentially includes a lot of record-breaking performers on the music scene. Among them all, we decided to opt for The Destiny’s Child and Dolly Parton, denoting respectively a girl music group whose success in the hip-hop scene easily spread around the  world, and a Tennessee girl turning her music into the soundtrack of the American country tradition. The project we were able to carry on thanks to the Melody Unibo visualizations and graphics allowed us to bring to life many of the things we wanted to tell about our chosen music icons and also to discover a lot of information we were not aware of. 
    <br>
    <br>If you are interested in knowing more about how we developed our project, what information we focused on and how the Melody graphics look like, we invite you to scroll down this webpage and enjoy our stories. 
    <br>
  </h1>
    </p>
