<!-- First Story Section -->
    <div class="w3-content w3-justify w3-text-grey w3-padding-64" id="about">
    <h2 class="w3-text-light-grey">Melody story 1: The Destiny's Child's Records</h2>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Our story aims at providing an overview of the amount of girl bands that have populated the music scene since the very beginning of the last century. Girl bands, especially the ones who have their origins in the United States of America, are many and diverse. This is the reason why, after delineating very briefly the amount of girl bands, the number of members they are (and were) composed of, we decided to focus on a particular girl band whose career is marked by an impressive amount of records and hits: The Destiny’s Child.
    </p>
    <br>
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Over the past decades, girl groups have been an integral part of the music industry, exerting a profound influence on the musical landscape and creating timeless hits. Today, their presence has grown exponentially, with a staggering number of over six hundred girl groups thriving worldwide.
    </p>
    <img src="img/image.jpg.png" width="800" height="500">
     
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity"> 
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p> 
    <p>The term "girl group" also denotes the wave of American female pop singing groups who flourished in the late 1950s and early 1960s.
    </p>
    <img src="img/a.jpg.png" width="800" height="500">
    
    
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity"> 
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p> 
    <p>Girl Bands find their origins in different historical periods. However, the peak of girl band creation is clearly at the very beginning of the 90s. During this time, a significant number of Girl Bands emerged, with many of them typically featuring a three-member lineup.
    </p>
    <img src="img/ab.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">
    <br>
    <br>
     <img src="img/abc.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">

     <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity"> 
    <p>A particular band we decided to analyze is the multi-award winning all-female group The Destiny’s Child. The members are: LeToya Luckett, Farrah Franklin, Beyoncé, Michelle Williams, Kelly Rowland and LaTavia Roberson. They perform mainly hyp hop music and rhythm and blues. 
    </p> 
    <img src="img/abcd.jpg.png" width="800" height="800"

    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity"> 
    <p> Destiny's Child recorded mainly R&B and hip hop songs with styles that encompass urban, contemporary, and dance-pop.
    </p> 
    <img src="img/abcde.jpg.png" width="800" height="680">

    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity"> 
    <p> The group boasts an extensive and remarkable discography, encompassing a vast array of musical achievements. In addition to their collaborations, compilations, and individual tracks, they released a total of 21 studio albums throughout their active years.
   </p> 
    <img src="img/m.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">

     <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p>In addition to numerous nominations, the Destiny's Child received many awards across various categories. They were recognized for their exceptional talent, captivating music videos, mesmerizing dance routines, and outstanding performances overall.
    </p>
    <img src="img/n.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">
     
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p>One of the last big shows where Destiny's Child performed together is the Super Bowl XLVII halftime show, which became the then second most watched show in Super Bowl history with 110.8 million viewers.
    </p>
    <img src="img/zyzy.png" width="800" height="650">
    </header>
  <!-- End First Story Section -->

  <!-- Second Story Section -->
   <div class="w3-content w3-justify w3-text-grey w3-padding-64" id="about">
    <h2 class="w3-text-light-grey">Melody story 2: Dolly Parton, the Queen of Country music</h2>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Country is a music genre originating in the Southern and Southwestern United States.</p>
    <img src="img/zzz.png" width="800" height="700">
    
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p>Since the early 20th century, Tennessee has been home to many popular singers and it has been recognized worldwide as the capital of country music.
   </p>
   <img src="img/o.jpg.png" width="800" height="400">
   <br>
   <br>
   <img src="img/p.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">

    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
   <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>When talking about Tennessee, it is impossible not to mention the Queen of country music: Dolly Parton.
    </p>
    <img src="img/l.jpg.png" width="800" height="600">

    <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
    <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>The peak of her career started in the 1970s and continued in the new millennium. Dolly Parton, with a career spanning over 50 years, produced many successful albums starting from the early seventies, till the new millennium. Her discography includes studio, collaborative, live, soundtrack and compilation albums.
   </p>
   <img src="img/z.jpg.png" width="800" height="400">

   <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
   <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Dolly Parton, the iconic Queen of Country Music, has received many different typology of awards, which qualify her not only as a very successful singer, but also as an actor and a very influential public personality in general. Beyond the many recognitions, she received many nominations as well, which further identify the Country Music Queen as a very multifaceted and versatile performer.
   </p>
   <img src="img/wy.jpg.png" width="800" height="400">
   <br>
   <br>
   <img src="img/lmno.png" width="800" height="700">
   <br>
   <br>
   <img src="img/hk.jpg.png" width="800" height="700">

   <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
   <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Dolly Parton played a significant role in the Disney Channel TV series Hannah Montana, where she interprets the character of Hannah's (Miley Cyrus) aunt from Tennessee. The bond between them extends beyond the screen, as Dolly has a deep connection with Miley's father, Billy Ray Cyrus, and is also Miley's godmother. Furthermore, Miley herself has risen to become one of the most renowned performers of the present decade, with her work being notably influenced by the illustrious career of Dolly Parton.
   </p>
   <img src="img/www.jpg.png" width="800" height="600">

   <hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
   <p style="text-align:center ;"></p>
    <p>Apart from the roles on the screen, Dolly Parton is mainly known for her successful songs, all of them having a deep country sound. Many of these compositions feature deeply personal and introspective lyrics, drawing inspiration from her own life experiences, much like the iconic track "Jolene".
   </p>
   <img src="img/sss.jpg.png" width="800" height="650">
  </header>
