<h3 class="w3-text-light-grey">Methodology: Melody, Wikidata, Data Sources - Challenges</h3>
<hr style="width:200px" class="w3-opacity">
<h4 class="w3-text-light-grey">Melody</h4>
<p><b>Pros</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>The graphics of Melody is easy to understand and it is aesthetic</li>
  <li>The fact that it is possible to see the queries even if the story is published and visible to anyone is useful - it would be even better if it would be possible to see them for everything in the story (ex. Map, counter, etc.) </li>
  <li>Possibility of creating very rich and detailed tables</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>As a group, we found it difficult to work on Melody stories, as we could only work from one account on a single computer. It could be useful to work on the same story or project from different devices all together.</li>
  <li>It would be useful if we could save the project when we are working on it without publishing it, since sometimes it takes a lot to be saved and to see the latest uploaded version.</li>
  <li>Some bugs: when we used the arrows to move the items up and down, they often got deleted. </li>
</ul>
<br>
<h4 class="w3-text-light-grey">Wikidata</h4>
<p><b>Pros</b></p>
<ul>
 <li>Some items are easy to find and have a useful list of properties associated with them;</li>
 <li>The colors in the wikidata syntax are very useful for distinguishing the labels, the optional items and the items.</li>
 <li>Wikidata offers you many examples in different languages, through which it is possible to find some useful properties and items.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Cons</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>It was not easy to find results. Even if the queries were correct, the corpus didn’t have enough results or sources in order to give us numbers that were useful. </li>
  <li>We had difficulties sometimes to find the correct queries. Ex “singer” gave us problems, and we used “musician” even if it is a more general and broader category.</li>
  <li>Wikidata signals when you make a mistake in the query, however it does not specify the error. </li>
  <li>Difficulty in finding the right properties, for example in distinguishing between P27 (country of citizenship), P276 (location), P495 (from), P19/P131* (resident in the territorial entity of), and the ones for the authorship of the songs, which ended up being “lyrics by”, P676, and not “is the author of” or “written by”. </li>
</ul>
<br>
<h4 class="w3-text-light-grey">Data Sources</h4>
<p>We started by doing some searches on the Polifonia corpus with the MusicBo module. However, we could not find much information about the artists we had in mind to analyze. MusicBo offers much data about music in Bologna and classical music in general, however, it was not possible to retrieve information about music in the world, so we opted for the Wikidata knowledge graph in general. MusicBo was useful for doing our first researches.</p>


